My thoughts on the first (and probably hardest!) week of the 21-Day Sugar Detox:

<br>

<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/RTJv6hC-lkE" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>

<br>

**What I've Learned This Week:**

1. I am more hungry when I do not eat sugar. I guess that means I should be eating more real food...

2. It is not just sugar that is the culprit - chips have been calling my name!

3. The weekends are hard - make yourself a (21DSD approved!) treat. 


**The Treat I Tried:**

[Bittersweet Dark Chocolate Almond Butter Cups](http://21daysugardetox.com/recipes/21dsd-recipe-chocolate-almond-butter-cups/)



